## **Task Objective**
- Format team data in a structured **data frame/table**.
- Use **Python or R** without **loops, conditionals, or functions**.
- Ensure readability and ease of data retrieval.

---

## **Implementation Approach**
We utilize **data frames**, a fundamental concept in data science, to organize team information efficiently.

---

## **Code Implementation**
### **Python Implementation (Pandas DataFrame)**
```python
import pandas as pd

# Create structured data
team_data = pd.DataFrame({
    "Name": ["Musa Al Hassan Kromah", "Nina Julian", "Fowowe Toyin"],
    "Slack_Username": ["Musa", "Julian", "Toyin"],
    "Email": ["kromahmusa86@gmail.com", "anyangonina39@gmail.com", "toyintoyo05@gmail.com"],
    "Hobby": ["Hiking", "Listening to Music", "Reading"],
    "Country": ["Liberia", "Kenya", "Nigeria"],
    "Discipline": ["Biotechnology", "Biotechnology", "Biochemistry"],
    "Preferred_Language": ["Python, R", "R", "Python"]
})

# Print formatted data
print(team_data)

## R Implementation (Data Frame)
# Load necessary library
data <- data.frame(
  Name = c("Musa Al Hassan Kromah", "Nina Julian", "Fowowe Toyin"),
  Slack_Username = c("Musa", "Julian", "Toyin"),
  Email = c("kromahmusa86@gmail.com", "anyangonina39@gmail.com", "toyintoyo05@gmail.com"),
  Hobby = c("Hiking", "Listening to Music", "Reading"),
  Country = c("Liberia", "Kenya", "Nigeria"),
  Discipline = c("Biotechnology", "Biotechnology", "Biochemistry"),
  Preferred_Language = c("Python, R", "R", "Python")
)

# Print the data
print(data)

## Outcome
A structured representation of team information, ensuring clarity and accessibility.



